00:01:53.100 --> 00:01:54.620
So when you finish a line,

00:01:54.620 --> 00:01:56.700
I'm just going to add another striped line

00:01:56.700 --> 00:01:57.700
down the side.

00:01:57.700 --> 00:01:59.260
And then I'm going to keep building!

00:01:59.500 --> 00:02:01.260
So if you notice the hexes,

00:02:01.280 --> 00:02:03.120
I'm trying to position them

00:02:03.120 --> 00:02:04.860
so that they kinda interlock

00:02:04.860 --> 00:02:06.180
with each other.

00:02:06.180 --> 00:02:07.500
But they're not completely...

00:02:07.740 --> 00:02:08.480
touching,

00:02:08.480 --> 00:02:09.520
or overlapping.

00:02:09.520 --> 00:02:11.360
You can really push them together

00:02:11.360 --> 00:02:13.220
as tight as you want them to be.

00:02:13.220 --> 00:02:14.640
I like to leave a little space,

00:02:14.640 --> 00:02:16.540
so I can re-jig it or move it around

00:02:16.540 --> 00:02:17.540
if I need to.

00:02:17.680 --> 00:02:18.180
So,

00:02:18.180 --> 00:02:18.800
the pattern

00:02:18.800 --> 00:02:20.440
that I'm actually making,

00:02:20.440 --> 00:02:21.460
is supposed to be...

00:02:21.600 --> 00:02:23.940
a downwards "V" shape?

00:02:24.180 --> 00:02:26.040
So that's how you kinda see,

00:02:26.040 --> 00:02:26.540
like,

00:02:26.540 --> 00:02:28.280
if you look at the pink, for example.

00:02:28.300 --> 00:02:30.620
It's kinda going in one direction?

00:02:30.620 --> 00:02:31.300
It's like,

00:02:31.300 --> 00:02:31.980
slanted.

00:02:31.980 --> 00:02:33.560
It's not straight across the nail.

00:02:34.040 --> 00:02:35.620
And then on the OTHER half of the nail,

00:02:35.620 --> 00:02:36.380
I'm gonna do it

00:02:36.440 --> 00:02:37.080
going...

00:02:37.720 --> 00:02:39.000
same downwards...

00:02:39.000 --> 00:02:39.880
direction...

00:02:39.880 --> 00:02:40.520
Err, actually,

00:02:40.520 --> 00:02:41.580
upwards.

